WEBVTT

00:00.109 --> 00:01.437
<i>Previously, on "Bitten"...</i>

00:01.461 --> 00:03.484
You've not been to your apartment
since you've been back.

00:03.508 --> 00:05.468
You've moved in here by stealth, right?

00:05.492 --> 00:06.531
Elena: Zachary Cain.

00:06.555 --> 00:07.679
Clay: Something's not right.

00:07.703 --> 00:09.758
Cain's not smart enough
to come up with a plan.

00:09.790 --> 00:10.923
Karl Marsten.

00:10.925 --> 00:13.266
- Since when did Mutts work together?
- Never.

00:13.298 --> 00:15.172
Marsten and Cain are building an army.

00:15.193 --> 00:16.860
Everything they're doing

00:16.894 --> 00:18.750
is because of you, Clay.

00:19.670 --> 00:21.104
What do you want, Mr. Boggs?

00:21.106 --> 00:23.206
I want what you got.
Word is, Pack's weak.

00:23.208 --> 00:25.775
There's only one way to become top dog.

00:25.777 --> 00:27.644
(Mixed grunts)

00:27.646 --> 00:29.879
Jeremy and the others haven't
been entirely honest with you.

00:29.881 --> 00:32.415
- What, and you have?
- Clay is out of control.

00:32.418 --> 00:34.017
(Grunting)

00:34.019 --> 00:35.718
No more half-measures.

00:35.720 --> 00:37.219
You really think that's necessary?

00:37.221 --> 00:39.488
I want word to get out
that if you come at me...

00:39.490 --> 00:40.823
(Cracking)
Ahhh!

00:40.825 --> 00:42.358
there will be serious consequences.

00:42.360 --> 00:44.827
- Clay, what's wrong?
- I've done things.

00:44.829 --> 00:47.030
Necessary things.

00:47.032 --> 00:49.298
I feel like I'm barely
holding my head above water.

00:49.300 --> 00:50.800
I want to be a better man, Elena.

00:50.802 --> 00:52.435
<i>Please come home.</i>

00:52.437 --> 00:54.236
Dennis Stillwell is dead.

00:54.238 --> 00:55.337
What about Joey?

00:55.339 --> 00:57.273
There's only one body.
They took his eyes.

00:59.443 --> 01:01.044
Woman: The blond woman you came in with,

01:01.045 --> 01:02.511
she left a few minutes ago.

01:04.313 --> 01:06.982
You're not going to like what's inside.

01:12.755 --> 01:15.423
Antonio: Are we positive these
came from Dennis Stillwell?

01:15.425 --> 01:17.258
I saw his body.

01:17.260 --> 01:19.861
His eyes were gouged out. Those are his.

01:19.863 --> 01:21.063
<i>Were</i> his.

01:21.065 --> 01:23.599
Santos is going to pay dearly for this.

01:23.601 --> 01:25.633
(Cellphone chiming)

01:25.635 --> 01:27.068
Sorry, I'll just...

01:27.070 --> 01:29.637
(Chiming continues)

01:29.639 --> 01:31.239
You going to answer that?

01:35.911 --> 01:37.212
Hello?

01:40.349 --> 01:41.983
Why don't you ask him yourself?

01:44.219 --> 01:45.319
Go ahead.

01:47.489 --> 01:48.856
How did you like my gift?

01:48.858 --> 01:50.091
Jeremy: <i>You sick bastard.</i>

01:50.093 --> 01:52.093
Why did you kill Dennis Stillwell?

01:52.095 --> 01:54.028
Santos: <i>Technically it wasn't me.</i>

01:54.030 --> 01:55.863
But you've got to admit,

01:55.865 --> 01:57.364
it's an attention grabber.

01:57.366 --> 02:00.134
- You have my attention.
<i>- Good.</i>

02:00.136 --> 02:03.303
Because I want to be heard,
and taken seriously.

02:03.305 --> 02:05.038
Well, it'll be hard for you to talk

02:05.040 --> 02:06.706
after I rip your throat out.

02:06.708 --> 02:08.609
(Laugh)
You see,

02:08.610 --> 02:11.545
now, that is what we need
to be talking about.

02:11.547 --> 02:14.781
<i>The violent ways with which</i>
<i>you uphold the Pack laws.</i>

02:14.783 --> 02:17.250
Now you know how it feels
to be on the receiving end.

02:17.252 --> 02:19.485
<i>All that my associates and I want</i>

02:19.487 --> 02:21.788
<i>is to get out from underneath</i>
<i>the Pack's oppressive rule.</i>

02:21.790 --> 02:24.624
The rules of our society have
been established for centuries.

02:24.626 --> 02:27.127
What makes you think we'd be
interested in changing them now?

02:27.129 --> 02:29.328
Well, I'm sure you're not, Antonio,

02:29.330 --> 02:31.063
since you're the ones in power.

02:31.065 --> 02:32.498
<i>But there are a number of us who think</i>

02:32.500 --> 02:34.900
<i>it's about time for a new world order.</i>

02:34.902 --> 02:36.335
<i>If you don't agree, that's fine.</i>

02:36.337 --> 02:38.371
But you can count on
having some more funerals.

02:38.373 --> 02:40.806
What have you done with Joey Stillwell?

02:40.808 --> 02:42.408
<i>He's safe for now.</i>

02:42.410 --> 02:44.043
<i>Still has all his body parts,</i>

02:44.045 --> 02:46.245
<i>which is more than I can</i>
<i>say for Samuel Boggs.</i>

02:46.247 --> 02:48.047
Boggs thought we were weak.

02:48.049 --> 02:49.648
He needed to be taught a lesson.

02:49.650 --> 02:52.785
Dennis Stillwell thought we
were second class citizens.

02:52.787 --> 02:54.653
He was taught a lesson as well.

02:54.655 --> 02:57.289
Jeremy: <i>What do you want?</i>

02:57.291 --> 02:58.490
A meeting.

02:58.492 --> 03:00.458
<i>You and I get together, hash things out.</i>

03:00.460 --> 03:02.460
Great. Come to Stonehaven, we'll talk.

03:02.462 --> 03:05.063
You still haven't gotten the
blood stains out of your carpet

03:05.065 --> 03:07.165
from the last Santos
that was killed there.

03:07.167 --> 03:09.100
<i>I was thinking we could</i>
<i>meet at the park,</i>

03:09.102 --> 03:11.369
<i>on the east side of Bear Valley.</i>

03:11.371 --> 03:13.305
That doesn't work for me.

03:13.307 --> 03:16.241
Then please, select a location
other than your fortress.

03:16.243 --> 03:18.443
<i>I'll come alone, and in good faith.</i>

03:18.445 --> 03:21.579
<i>I'll trust you to do the same.</i>

03:21.581 --> 03:22.847
Fine.

03:22.849 --> 03:24.082
There's an abandoned campground

03:24.084 --> 03:25.516
just off county road 35.

03:25.518 --> 03:27.218
There's a pavilion on the west side.

03:27.220 --> 03:28.485
I'll meet you there.

03:28.487 --> 03:31.089
Sounds good to me. How about tomorrow,

03:31.091 --> 03:33.224
<i>say noon?</i>

03:33.226 --> 03:35.259
I'll see you there.

03:35.261 --> 03:36.460
Good.

03:36.462 --> 03:37.561
(Beep)

03:37.563 --> 03:39.129
You can't trust anything he says.

03:39.131 --> 03:40.331
Jeremy: No, I know that.

03:40.333 --> 03:41.532
We can't just sit here

03:41.534 --> 03:43.400
and let them pick us off one by one.

03:43.402 --> 03:46.036
We have to find a way to turn
this meeting into our advantage,

03:46.038 --> 03:48.038
maybe get a lead on where
that warehouse is.

03:48.040 --> 03:49.840
Clay and Elena, you head there now.

03:49.842 --> 03:51.375
Find stakeout positions.

03:51.377 --> 03:54.877
( ♪ )

03:59.351 --> 04:01.017
- You all right?
- I'll be fine

04:01.019 --> 04:02.552
once Santos and the others are put down.

04:02.554 --> 04:05.288
I'm talking about your phone call, Clay.

04:07.759 --> 04:09.792
What was that all about?

04:09.794 --> 04:11.728
I was... just having a rough time

04:11.730 --> 04:13.062
with some Mutt discipline.

04:13.064 --> 04:15.064
I thought that was
second nature for you.

04:15.066 --> 04:17.500
It's not the same as it used to be.

04:19.370 --> 04:21.870
Are you all right now?

04:21.873 --> 04:23.673
I'm better now that you're here.

04:25.976 --> 04:29.812
I came because of Dennis.

04:29.814 --> 04:31.647
And Santos.

04:38.989 --> 04:42.489
( ♪ )

04:47.331 --> 04:49.298
I've got a vantage point
on the south side.

04:49.300 --> 04:51.232
Clay: (On phone) <i>I found
a spot on the north end</i>

04:51.234 --> 04:53.669
but it's too exposed.
I'm going to keep scouting.

04:55.672 --> 04:58.407
I want to be ready for
whatever Santos has in store.

