05:49.931 --> 05:52.099
Philip: Hey, Sylvie. It's Philip.

05:52.101 --> 05:54.400
I was wondering if you could help me

05:54.402 --> 05:55.736
find someone who posted a video.

05:55.738 --> 05:58.971
I've tried to track them
down myself, but...

05:58.973 --> 06:01.207
No, no. No, you don't have to come over,

06:01.209 --> 06:02.775
it's... if you could just...

06:05.713 --> 06:06.912
An hour.

06:06.914 --> 06:08.681
Yeah, I'll be here.

06:10.016 --> 06:12.118
Looking forward to seeing you too.

06:22.695 --> 06:26.598
Antonio: I'm thinking of
booking Serenity of the Seas.

06:26.600 --> 06:28.167
Ah, two months?

06:28.169 --> 06:29.802
Six continents?

06:29.804 --> 06:31.403
Well, that sounds perfect.

06:33.339 --> 06:35.707
Yes, that's right, Stillwell.

06:37.777 --> 06:39.344
All right, thank you. I...

06:39.346 --> 06:40.679
I look forward to it.

06:43.516 --> 06:44.716
(Sigh)

06:44.718 --> 06:46.319
Sounds like Dennis is going on a cruise.

06:46.320 --> 06:48.119
A really nice one too.

06:48.121 --> 06:50.621
My guy posing as him is
in for a hell of a trip.

06:50.623 --> 06:54.025
Closing out someone's life
with a couple of calls...

06:54.027 --> 06:56.727
- What a thankless job.
- Ah, but necessary.

06:56.729 --> 06:59.530
We don't want the other families
alarmed about these deaths.

06:59.532 --> 07:01.800
You know, I never envied
you being Pack fixer.

07:01.802 --> 07:04.268
It's not so bad, once you
take out the emotion

07:04.270 --> 07:07.371
and focus on the necessity of it.

07:07.373 --> 07:09.173
You know, I always
figured you'd take over.

07:09.175 --> 07:10.775
I wouldn't be any good at that.

07:10.777 --> 07:12.042
Too much responsibility.

07:12.044 --> 07:13.977
You could handle it.

07:13.979 --> 07:15.279
You could, but you don't want to.

07:15.281 --> 07:17.481
I'm not like you, Dad.

07:17.483 --> 07:19.082
Okay, when you were my age,

07:19.084 --> 07:20.583
you already had a teenage kid.

07:20.585 --> 07:22.319
I don't know how you did it.

07:22.321 --> 07:24.421
I just adapted the circumstances

07:24.423 --> 07:26.223
and made the best of it.

07:26.225 --> 07:27.557
You'll see someday,

07:27.559 --> 07:30.127
you'll have a son of your own.

07:30.129 --> 07:33.063
I might already and not even know it.

07:33.065 --> 07:34.731
Okay, I hope you're kidding about that

07:34.733 --> 07:36.733
because we can't afford to
take these things lightly.

07:36.735 --> 07:38.335
I know, I'm kidding.

07:41.271 --> 07:43.707
But there was that one night in Rio

07:43.709 --> 07:45.442
with a set of twins,

07:45.444 --> 07:48.177
and the details are
kind of hazy, I mean...

07:48.179 --> 07:49.813
Last time you said it was triplets.

07:49.815 --> 07:52.415
I'm sorry, I overreacted.

07:52.417 --> 07:53.816
It's okay, you were scared.

07:53.818 --> 07:55.651
Yeah, well, after seeing
those people in the ER

07:55.653 --> 07:57.820
with real emergencies,
I felt ridiculous.

07:57.822 --> 07:59.555
Hey, listen,

07:59.557 --> 08:01.991
you're pregnant for the first time,

08:01.993 --> 08:03.592
and you were in pain.

08:03.594 --> 08:05.761
You can't take that lightly.

08:05.763 --> 08:06.929
And honestly,

08:06.931 --> 08:09.232
if the doctor prescribed
a little bed rest for me,

08:09.234 --> 08:10.532
I'd take it.

08:11.901 --> 08:13.201
(Sigh)

08:14.103 --> 08:15.704
Hey, what's wrong, baby?

08:25.248 --> 08:26.748
It's not my first time.

08:28.351 --> 08:30.185
When I was younger, I was with this guy,

08:30.187 --> 08:32.587
and things got heavy kind of fast.

08:32.589 --> 08:34.389
I wasn't prepared for it.

08:34.390 --> 08:36.291
And you got pregnant.

08:36.293 --> 08:38.458
I never meant to keep it a secret, okay?

08:38.461 --> 08:41.596
- I'm sorry I never told you.
- No, no, that's okay.

08:41.597 --> 08:44.131
What happened?

08:44.133 --> 08:46.100
When he found out he split,

08:46.102 --> 08:49.504
just disappeared out of my life.

08:49.506 --> 08:52.573
I was completely alone and...

08:52.575 --> 08:54.709
the stress was too much for me.

08:54.711 --> 08:56.977
A few weeks later I had a miscarriage.

08:59.247 --> 09:01.448
It was the low point of my life.

09:02.350 --> 09:04.385
So I'm scared.

09:04.387 --> 09:06.086
I'm scared that me being pregnant

09:06.088 --> 09:07.922
is going to drive you away and...

09:10.591 --> 09:12.159
I'm going to be alone again.

09:12.161 --> 09:13.794
Listen to me.

09:15.363 --> 09:17.931
There is nothing...

09:17.933 --> 09:21.134
nothing for you to be scared of.

09:21.136 --> 09:22.769
You are fine,

09:22.771 --> 09:24.370
the baby's fine, and we're fine.

09:24.372 --> 09:25.906
We're better than fine.

09:28.175 --> 09:30.844
And I'm not going anywhere.

09:30.846 --> 09:32.378
I promise you that.

09:40.054 --> 09:42.655
(Ominous ♪)

09:42.657 --> 09:46.157
( ♪ )

09:50.364 --> 09:52.631
Clay: (On phone) <i>- You seeing this?</i>
- Got it.

09:57.804 --> 09:59.638
Check out the box.

09:59.640 --> 10:02.675
It looks like the same wrapping
as the other one from Santos.

10:02.677 --> 10:06.177
( ♪ )

10:20.726 --> 10:22.727
Jeremy, we've got a situation.

10:22.729 --> 10:24.629
<i>Some kid just dropped off a box</i>

10:24.631 --> 10:27.966
<i>wrapped in the same paper</i>
<i>as Stillwell's eyes.</i>

10:27.968 --> 10:29.166
Elena, don't touch it.

10:29.168 --> 10:31.569
Antonio and I are on our way.

10:31.571 --> 10:33.137
Could be Joey's body parts.

10:33.139 --> 10:35.239
- Could be a booby trap.
- Exactly.

10:35.241 --> 10:36.541
Nick, you stay and watch the property.

10:36.543 --> 10:38.976
We're going to head out there.

10:38.978 --> 10:41.479
(Snarling)

10:46.351 --> 10:48.452
(Knocking on door)

10:52.991 --> 10:54.392
I come bearing dark roast,

10:54.394 --> 10:56.660
fat free muffins, and the keys

10:56.662 --> 10:58.862
to unlocking the secret of the internet.

11:01.065 --> 11:03.266
Are you going to invite me in?

11:03.268 --> 11:04.935
Come on in.
(Chuckling)

11:04.937 --> 11:07.404
Thanks, handsome.

11:08.372 --> 11:10.273
(Sigh)

11:10.275 --> 11:11.707
You haven't changed a bit, Sylvie.

11:11.709 --> 11:13.609
That's a good thing, right?

11:14.912 --> 11:16.812
Those wolves are beautiful animals.

11:16.814 --> 11:19.215
Philip: Pshh, yeah, but so brutal.

11:19.217 --> 11:20.583
Any luck tracking down that person

11:20.585 --> 11:22.152
- who posted the video?
- Yeah,

11:22.154 --> 11:24.820
I've got an email address
associated with the username.

11:24.822 --> 11:26.689
I'll have the rest of
the info in a few minutes.

11:26.691 --> 11:28.991
Do I want to know how you're doing this?

11:28.993 --> 11:30.826
Mm, no.

11:35.866 --> 11:37.567
New girlfriend?

11:37.569 --> 11:39.602
How's everything at Bancroft Worldwide?

11:39.604 --> 11:42.438
Ehh, it's boring since you left.

11:42.440 --> 11:45.240
Does she live with you?

11:45.242 --> 11:48.043
It's a simple yes or no. The
questions get harder in round two.

11:48.045 --> 11:49.678
She's just moved in.

11:49.680 --> 11:51.447
Does she make you happy?

11:53.716 --> 11:55.750
Yeah.

11:55.752 --> 11:56.851
If you say so.

11:58.254 --> 12:00.289
Nate Parker.

12:00.291 --> 12:02.356
- Excuse me?
- The guy who posted the video.

12:02.358 --> 12:04.693
And, based on his
labyrinthian security system,

12:04.695 --> 12:06.461
he's a real wirehead.

12:06.463 --> 12:09.397
Normally, I'd have been through
those firewalls in half the time.

12:09.399 --> 12:11.132
Let's see...

12:11.134 --> 12:12.366
Oh.

12:12.368 --> 12:14.970
Also, he appears to be
a bit of a nut job.

12:14.972 --> 12:18.306
He's written over 100 emails
to government officials.

12:18.308 --> 12:20.341
Great.

12:20.343 --> 12:21.709
His last known address

12:21.711 --> 12:23.544
is an apartment in Corktown.

12:25.414 --> 12:26.947
So what now?

12:26.949 --> 12:29.350
Well, my client wants me to
buy the rights to the video

12:29.352 --> 12:31.452
so we can use them in his ad campaign.

12:31.454 --> 12:33.321
- I'll go with you.
- No, it's all right.

12:33.323 --> 12:35.089
- I'll... I'll go.
- Philip,

12:35.091 --> 12:37.658
you're intelligent and
beautiful and everything,

12:37.660 --> 12:40.628
but this guy is suspicious
of the government.

12:40.630 --> 12:42.429
He sees you and all he'll see is a suit,

12:42.431 --> 12:44.464
- and he'll shut down.
- I'll dress casual.

12:44.466 --> 12:46.133
Babe, you could go in there naked

12:46.135 --> 12:47.601
and he'd still see a suit.

12:47.603 --> 12:51.004
I can speak his language,
so he'll trust me.

12:51.006 --> 12:52.606
You need me. Admit it.

12:56.777 --> 13:00.277
( ♪ )

13:11.425 --> 13:12.759
Jeremy: Oh, no.

13:12.761 --> 13:14.560
We really should keep going, Jeremy.

13:14.562 --> 13:16.629
She needs our help first.

13:28.575 --> 13:29.975
(Snarling, grunting)

13:29.977 --> 13:31.577
Elena: Cain...

13:38.485 --> 13:39.685
Come on.

13:39.687 --> 13:41.186
(Cellphone buzzing)

13:43.303 --> 13:45.223
- Yeah.
Antonio: (On phone) <i>- Yeah, we're on our way,</i>

13:45.225 --> 13:46.792
but we came across an accident.

13:46.794 --> 13:48.459
Clay: <i>An accident? Is everything okay?</i>

13:48.461 --> 13:49.828
I'll let you know.

13:49.830 --> 13:51.529
Recorded voice: <i>All circuits are busy...</i>

13:51.531 --> 13:52.931
Damn it!

13:52.933 --> 13:56.433
( ♪ )

13:58.938 --> 14:00.505
What happened?

14:00.507 --> 14:02.440
Are you okay? Can you hear me?

14:02.442 --> 14:05.476
...car came out of
nowhere... took off...

14:05.478 --> 14:08.246
Antonio: Yeah, looks like the
girl's in really bad shape.

14:08.248 --> 14:09.614
(Yelling in pain)

14:11.022 --> 14:13.204
(Grunt)
It's an ambush!

14:18.657 --> 14:20.558
(Mixed grunting)

14:23.463 --> 14:24.696
How bad is it?

14:24.698 --> 14:25.998
Both: Ahh!

14:28.401 --> 14:30.035
Ahh!

14:30.037 --> 14:32.371
(Grunting)
Nice to see you again, Antonio.

14:32.373 --> 14:34.373
Elena's voice: <i>Hi, you've almost
reached Elena Michaels...</i>

14:34.375 --> 14:36.340
Damn...

14:36.342 --> 14:38.075
(Snarling)

14:43.649 --> 14:46.150
(Mixed growling)

14:49.989 --> 14:53.357
(Mixed grunting)

14:53.359 --> 14:55.126
(Snarling)

14:59.297 --> 15:00.297
(Whimpering)

15:00.299 --> 15:01.865
Antonio and Jeremy are under attack!

15:01.867 --> 15:03.634
Go and find them.

15:10.942 --> 15:13.443
(Mixed grunting)

15:27.425 --> 15:28.958
Antonio!

15:28.960 --> 15:30.460
Aghh!

15:30.462 --> 15:31.561
(Grunting)

15:34.532 --> 15:37.400
(Tires screeching)

15:37.402 --> 15:39.569
Jeremy: Help Antonio.
He's been hurt badly.

15:43.273 --> 15:44.506
(Groaning)

15:44.508 --> 15:46.442
We have to get him back to Stonehaven.
Come on.

15:47.811 --> 15:50.112
(Groaning in pain)
There we go.

15:55.151 --> 15:57.086
Man: How did you, um, locate me?

15:57.088 --> 16:00.689
I ran a heat seeker on your username.

16:00.691 --> 16:03.225
No... no way.

16:03.227 --> 16:05.227
I've got asbestos firewalls.
(Laughing)

16:05.229 --> 16:08.363
Yeah, they're really
not all that fireproof.

16:08.365 --> 16:10.899
I found a race condition
in one of your logic gates

16:10.901 --> 16:13.034
and I just waltzed right
into your computer.

16:13.036 --> 16:14.335
Seriously?

16:16.005 --> 16:17.973
Damn.

16:17.975 --> 16:19.407
You guys are the government?

16:19.409 --> 16:20.875
Do we look like we're
from the government?

16:20.877 --> 16:22.644
- He does.
Philip: - No, like I told you,

16:22.646 --> 16:24.980
my ad agency wants to acquire
some of the footage you shot.

16:24.982 --> 16:26.547
Who says I'm interested in selling?

16:26.549 --> 16:28.850
I think your credit card company
might like a little payoff

16:28.852 --> 16:30.818
on some of your overdue accounts.

16:30.820 --> 16:32.186
Who says I'm overdue?

16:34.223 --> 16:36.757
Okay, got a few bills.

16:36.759 --> 16:38.526
How much money are we talking about?

16:38.528 --> 16:40.027
How does $2000 sound?

16:40.029 --> 16:41.862
(Laugh)
Are you serious? Is he serious?

16:41.864 --> 16:43.331
I mean, this is great stuff.

16:43.333 --> 16:44.965
Wolves running at Cherry Beach.

16:44.967 --> 16:46.601
I don't know. The quality's only fair

16:46.603 --> 16:48.836
and the camera work looks like
it's done by a 10-year-old.

16:48.838 --> 16:50.403
Oh, so... you track me down

16:50.405 --> 16:52.072
so you can come here and insult me?

16:52.074 --> 16:54.307
How cool would it be to
see your footage on TV?

16:54.309 --> 16:56.510
You're talking television,
I'm talking 10 grand.

16:56.512 --> 16:57.711
Five grand.

16:57.713 --> 16:59.613
And you hand over all
the footage you shot,

16:59.615 --> 17:01.214
you take down the video you posted,

17:01.216 --> 17:03.316
and you sign to me all your rights.

17:03.318 --> 17:04.416
$7500.

17:09.423 --> 17:12.291
Okay, five thou. But I want cash.

17:12.294 --> 17:13.393
Deal.

17:16.631 --> 17:18.498
(Tires screeching)

17:18.500 --> 17:21.834
( ♪ )

17:21.836 --> 17:23.435
What the hell happened?

17:23.436 --> 17:26.605
Your dad's in bad shape.
We have to get him inside.

17:26.607 --> 17:29.408
(Panting)
Dad...

17:35.049 --> 17:37.249
(Groaning)
You're going to be okay, Dad.

17:37.251 --> 17:40.052
- My God, are you...? - I'll be fine.
Help Clay get the medical supplies.

17:40.054 --> 17:41.353
We have to be fast.

17:43.190 --> 17:46.091
Antonio: (Groaning)

17:46.093 --> 17:48.327
Jeremy:
Clay, I need gauze, pads, and tape.

17:49.496 --> 17:51.597
Okay, give me some, quick.

17:51.599 --> 17:53.832
We need to keep pressure on this.

17:53.834 --> 17:56.034
Elena, I need rubbing alcohol.

17:56.036 --> 17:57.769
Thank you. It's going to sting...

17:57.771 --> 17:59.738
(Yelling)
Okay, cover it up.

17:59.740 --> 18:01.306
I need hemostatic powder.

18:01.308 --> 18:02.974
I need more gauze.

18:02.976 --> 18:05.811
(Groaning in pain)

18:05.813 --> 18:07.645
Jeremy: More pressure.

18:07.647 --> 18:08.880
Hang in there, Dad.

18:08.882 --> 18:10.748
- Nicky, listen to me.
- Yes.

18:10.750 --> 18:12.750
We're going to roll him and we're
going to wrap it back over, okay?

18:12.752 --> 18:15.453
Antonio: (Groaning in pain)
Okay, got it?

18:17.690 --> 18:19.056
Take this way...

18:19.058 --> 18:21.826
I'm going to need some scissors, Clay.

18:21.828 --> 18:23.228
Stay with us.

18:23.230 --> 18:26.964
Nicky: Hang in there, Dad.

18:26.966 --> 18:29.800
Antonio: (Groaning softly)

18:29.802 --> 18:31.501
Better?
(Coughing)

18:37.075 --> 18:38.609
I'll be okay, Nicky.

18:40.178 --> 18:42.646
We're going to track down Santos, okay?

18:42.648 --> 18:44.214
I know you will.

18:44.216 --> 18:46.550
How am I doing, doc?

18:46.552 --> 18:50.153
You're strong. You're going to be okay.

18:50.155 --> 18:53.223
You've never lied
to me before, my friend.

18:53.225 --> 18:55.892
Don't start now.

18:55.894 --> 18:59.062
I'm going to do everything I
can to get you through this.

18:59.064 --> 19:01.697
Okay.

19:01.699 --> 19:03.566
Ohh...

19:06.436 --> 19:09.936
( ♪ )

19:18.296 --> 19:20.765
Here you go.

19:22.509 --> 19:24.208
Hibiscus tea?

19:24.210 --> 19:25.944
Yeah, it's good for you.

19:25.946 --> 19:27.846
It's strong.

19:27.848 --> 19:29.280
It's too much?

19:29.282 --> 19:31.482
- We've got some chamomile.
- No, this is good.

19:31.484 --> 19:33.251
It'll replace my Cabernet cravings

19:33.253 --> 19:34.886
for the next six months.

19:34.888 --> 19:37.088
Yeah, and our little girl will come out

19:37.090 --> 19:38.523
with a taste for the finer things.

19:38.525 --> 19:40.525
(Giggling)
So you think it's a girl?

19:40.527 --> 19:42.627
- Definitely.
- And how can you be so sure?

19:42.629 --> 19:44.862
Well, you know, I have my
PhD, I know these things.

19:44.864 --> 19:47.898
I also know she's going to
come out and take after you.

19:47.900 --> 19:50.568
She'll be beautiful,

19:50.570 --> 19:52.736
talented, smart.

19:52.738 --> 19:55.239
(Cellphone ringing)

19:57.542 --> 19:58.942
You can get that.

19:58.944 --> 20:00.610
Just remember where we left off.

20:04.949 --> 20:06.684
- Going to get it?
- No, it's okay.

20:06.686 --> 20:08.518
We were just supposed to
go running this week.

20:08.520 --> 20:11.088
I'll just call her back later.

20:11.090 --> 20:13.223
- Sure?
- Positive.

20:14.525 --> 20:17.227
In that case, where were we?

20:24.702 --> 20:26.570
Logan's not answering.

20:26.572 --> 20:28.205
I don't want to text him with this,

20:28.207 --> 20:30.039
I'll just try later.

20:30.041 --> 20:32.508
Antonio: - Jeremy...
- Shh.

20:32.510 --> 20:35.011
We can talk later, Antonio.

20:35.013 --> 20:36.813
You have to stop them.

20:38.082 --> 20:39.548
We will.

20:39.550 --> 20:42.418
We will, you and I together.

20:42.420 --> 20:44.486
You and I together.

20:44.488 --> 20:45.588
(Gasp)

20:48.258 --> 20:50.226
Clay: Whoa, whoa, whoa! Jeremy, Jeremy.

20:50.228 --> 20:51.627
Come on...
(Grunting)

20:51.629 --> 20:53.095
Come on, come on.

20:53.097 --> 20:56.298
(Mixed chatter)

20:56.300 --> 20:58.200
Nicky: - This doesn't look good.
- I'm fine.

20:58.202 --> 21:00.336
Elena: - Tell me what to do.
- I'm fine.

21:00.338 --> 21:02.304
Jeremy, tell me what to do.

21:02.306 --> 21:05.640
Get some... get some
antiseptic and some gauze.

21:05.642 --> 21:07.642
- I got it, I got it.
- We need to stop the bleeding.

21:07.644 --> 21:09.510
Okay, we've just got to clean this out.

21:16.452 --> 21:18.586
(Indistinct comments)

21:18.588 --> 21:19.887
(Groaning)

21:25.127 --> 21:27.662
Sylvie: Do you think you have
enough here to build a campaign?

21:27.664 --> 21:30.097
I hope so. I wish there was a way

21:30.099 --> 21:31.766
to improve the quality, though.

21:31.768 --> 21:34.201
I have a program on my computer at home

21:34.203 --> 21:35.803
that can increase the clarity

21:35.805 --> 21:37.371
and pull some frame grabs.

21:37.373 --> 21:39.940
Really? That'd be amazing.

21:39.942 --> 21:42.910
Why don't you come over? We
could do it this afternoon.

21:42.912 --> 21:45.880
Or I could just send you a file.

21:45.882 --> 21:48.515
- I wasn't hitting on you.
- No, I know,

21:48.517 --> 21:52.086
I just have a lot of work
to do here, and there's...

21:52.088 --> 21:53.654
Philip, it's me.

21:53.656 --> 21:55.489
Clearly I'm making you uncomfortable.

21:55.491 --> 21:56.790
Yeah, it's a little awkward.

21:56.792 --> 21:58.525
There's no reason why it should be,

21:58.527 --> 22:00.260
not after all the time
we spent together.

22:00.262 --> 22:03.330
That's what makes it awkward.

22:03.332 --> 22:05.599
You have to admit, we make a good team.

22:05.601 --> 22:07.801
Mm-hmm, but not a good couple.

22:07.803 --> 22:09.169
But we could have.

22:09.171 --> 22:11.671
You never really gave it a chance.

22:11.673 --> 22:15.074
Why is that? I mean, we were
always great in bed, weren't we?

22:15.076 --> 22:17.777
Bed, kitchen counter,

22:17.779 --> 22:18.978
- balcony...
- Sylvie.

22:20.447 --> 22:22.315
I know! Sex isn't everything,

22:22.317 --> 22:25.351
and I know I can be a little
too intense, but still.

22:25.353 --> 22:28.187
What we had was great.

22:28.189 --> 22:31.824
But what I have now is...

22:31.826 --> 22:32.925
Better?

22:35.094 --> 22:36.395
For me.

22:41.134 --> 22:43.368
Well, she's a lucky girl.

22:43.370 --> 22:46.338
I hope she's everything
you ever wanted and more.

22:58.251 --> 23:01.185
Woman: (Moaning)

23:01.187 --> 23:03.988
You should have seen him, baby!

23:03.990 --> 23:05.857
Stabbed him in the leg!

23:05.859 --> 23:07.492
And then...

23:07.494 --> 23:09.661
the blood was flowing.

23:09.663 --> 23:11.363
Cain: Oh, you stabbed him real good, huh?

23:11.365 --> 23:13.197
Woman: You know it, baby!

23:13.199 --> 23:15.699
Both: (Loud moaning, grunting)

23:19.938 --> 23:21.739
(Laughing)

23:22.941 --> 23:24.041
(Sighing)

23:29.047 --> 23:31.115
That was amazing.

23:32.384 --> 23:35.185
You're amazing.
(Chuckling)

23:35.187 --> 23:38.555
Oh, honey, your cut opened up.

23:41.125 --> 23:44.060
(Laughing)
Does it turn you on?

23:44.062 --> 23:47.464
Everything about you turns me on.

23:47.466 --> 23:48.798
You want to go again?

23:48.800 --> 23:52.769
Ah, no one's ever tired me out before.

23:52.771 --> 23:55.571
Being with a werewolf is incredible.

23:57.574 --> 23:59.209
You can hold your own,

23:59.211 --> 24:01.311
for a human.

24:01.313 --> 24:03.313
I think that's a compliment.

24:03.315 --> 24:05.715
Definitely.

24:05.717 --> 24:07.583
You really didn't have to cut yourself.

24:07.585 --> 24:10.887
Mmm, I wanted it to be real.

24:10.889 --> 24:13.790
You said they could smell if the
blood was fake or real, right?

24:15.759 --> 24:18.327
I've never known anyone like you.

24:18.329 --> 24:20.062
Baby,

24:20.064 --> 24:23.065
I've definitely never
met anyone like you.

24:30.873 --> 24:34.373
( ♪ )

24:36.080 --> 24:37.712
He's bleeding internally.

24:37.714 --> 24:40.916
He's lost too much blood.

24:40.918 --> 24:42.551
Wh... what can we do?

24:42.553 --> 24:45.654
There's nothing more
that I can do for him.

24:45.656 --> 24:47.789
W... well then, let's get
him to a hospital.

24:47.791 --> 24:48.890
Nick!

24:50.192 --> 24:51.793
You know we can't do that.

24:51.795 --> 24:54.262
I'm not going to stand here
and watch my father die!

24:54.264 --> 24:55.830
Nicky, Nicky...

24:57.433 --> 24:58.732
You can't fight this fight.

24:59.868 --> 25:01.836
Mm... Elena...

25:05.374 --> 25:07.108
I'm here, Antonio.

25:08.510 --> 25:10.678
The boys need you.

25:15.416 --> 25:16.717
I know.

25:17.619 --> 25:19.520
Take care of them.

25:23.124 --> 25:25.158
Clay...

25:25.160 --> 25:26.460
Yeah.

25:27.795 --> 25:30.597
You find it in your heart to forgive.

25:32.367 --> 25:34.167
I... I will.

25:38.339 --> 25:40.507
My friend,

25:40.509 --> 25:42.976
no more half-measures.

25:42.978 --> 25:47.013
Santos, all of them...

25:47.015 --> 25:48.214
(Grunt)

25:48.216 --> 25:50.617
My friend...

25:50.619 --> 25:52.685
it's time for you to rest now.

25:55.088 --> 25:57.256
Nicholas.

25:57.258 --> 25:58.992
Nicky. I'm right here, Dad.

25:58.994 --> 26:01.127
Come closer.

26:01.129 --> 26:02.728
Closer.

26:05.432 --> 26:08.034
(Inaudible)

26:08.036 --> 26:11.536
( ♪ )

26:18.812 --> 26:20.078
Thank you.

26:21.548 --> 26:24.149
(Soft grunts)

26:24.151 --> 26:27.651
( ♪ )

26:35.995 --> 26:38.296
(Sobbing)

26:54.291 --> 26:55.991
30 years of friendship.

26:59.765 --> 27:00.898
(Sigh)

27:00.900 --> 27:04.836
So many little things you
take for granted, and then...

27:04.838 --> 27:05.937
suddenly it's over.

27:05.939 --> 27:09.140
These Mutts need to
be put down for good.

27:09.142 --> 27:10.709
I agree.

27:10.711 --> 27:12.376
No middle ground, no mercy.

27:12.378 --> 27:15.546
- Elena...
- They killed Pete, they killed Antonio.

27:15.548 --> 27:17.615
What more is it going to
take until we fight back?

27:21.987 --> 27:24.421
This is more than just
killing a few Mutts.

27:24.423 --> 27:25.656
Nick, we can talk about this later.

27:25.658 --> 27:27.725
No, I have the rest
of my life to grieve.

27:27.727 --> 27:29.293
We all do.

27:29.295 --> 27:32.529
Right now we need to
go on the offensive,

27:32.531 --> 27:34.398
find out who else is involved

27:34.400 --> 27:36.199
and just how far this reaches.

27:36.201 --> 27:38.636
We also need to find out who
that woman was at the ambush.

27:38.638 --> 27:40.203
Nick: The Mutts are getting desperate

27:40.205 --> 27:42.573
if they're bringing in humans
to do their dirty work.

27:42.575 --> 27:43.874
So where do we start?

27:45.542 --> 27:47.577
Cain. That's the weakest link.

27:47.579 --> 27:48.812
Cain's hardly weak.

27:48.814 --> 27:50.247
Yes, he is, he's mentally weak.

27:50.249 --> 27:51.481
He's sloppy, he's careless.

27:51.483 --> 27:54.151
We need to find him and get him to talk.

27:54.153 --> 27:55.518
I'll go to the campground,

27:55.520 --> 27:57.654
- see if I can pick up a scent.
- Not alone.

27:57.656 --> 27:59.489
You're going to go with Clay.

27:59.491 --> 28:01.591
Nick, you and I will stay

28:01.593 --> 28:03.426
to tend to Antonio's body.

28:06.229 --> 28:08.130
How's your wound?

28:08.132 --> 28:10.266
It's fine.

28:10.268 --> 28:11.567
Don't worry about me.

28:13.437 --> 28:17.206
I know how much he meant to you.

28:17.208 --> 28:19.308
To all of us.

28:19.310 --> 28:21.610
We can't bring Antonio back,

28:21.612 --> 28:23.645
but we can make this right.

28:35.525 --> 28:36.858
The box is gone.

28:39.429 --> 28:41.896
We were only here a few hours ago.

28:43.433 --> 28:45.567
Everything's changed.

28:49.038 --> 28:51.840
I can't stop thinking
about Antonio and Pete.

28:51.842 --> 28:56.010
I know, me neither.
They were my brothers.

28:59.481 --> 29:03.584
We aren't going to lose any more family.

29:03.586 --> 29:05.920
The only blood spilled
from this point on

29:05.922 --> 29:07.688
will be Mutt blood.

29:10.925 --> 29:13.794
(Sniffing)

29:13.796 --> 29:15.229
He went North.

29:22.738 --> 29:25.472
Did your father tell you where
he wanted his ashes spread?

29:27.408 --> 29:29.509
We never really discussed it.

29:29.511 --> 29:31.511
I guess neither of us
wanted to face the reality

29:31.513 --> 29:33.280
that one day...

29:33.282 --> 29:36.016
You know he always really loved the...

29:36.018 --> 29:39.920
He loved the cherry grove
on your family's estate.

29:39.922 --> 29:41.488
Uh, you'll have to forgive me.

29:41.490 --> 29:45.124
My stitching skills
are... a little rusty.

29:45.126 --> 29:46.993
(Vehicle approaching)

29:48.629 --> 29:50.963
You go get that. I'll finish this up.

29:50.965 --> 29:52.064
Go.

29:56.069 --> 29:57.270
(Knocking on door)

30:06.179 --> 30:08.281
- Sheriff.
- Mr. Sorrentino.

30:10.450 --> 30:12.551
Clayton Danvers here?

30:12.553 --> 30:14.720
He had some business to attend to.

30:14.722 --> 30:16.455
Is there anything I can help you with?

30:16.457 --> 30:19.257
Is Jeremy Danvers home?

30:19.259 --> 30:22.661
It's, uh, it's not a good time.

30:22.663 --> 30:24.730
It's never a good time
to talk to the police,

30:24.732 --> 30:25.997
but we have a situation on our hands.

30:25.999 --> 30:27.933
We found Michael Braxton's body.

30:29.669 --> 30:31.369
- His body.
- That's right.

30:31.371 --> 30:33.871
- Morning, Sheriff.
- Mr. Danvers.

30:33.873 --> 30:36.507
I was just asking about you.

30:36.509 --> 30:39.244
Nick, could we have a moment?

30:39.246 --> 30:41.079
Would you like to come in?

30:41.081 --> 30:42.180
Thanks.

30:49.621 --> 30:52.222
See you in a few days.

30:52.224 --> 30:54.258
Who was it, baby?

30:54.260 --> 30:56.461
Santos.

30:56.463 --> 30:58.162
He and LeBlanc are headed to Manhattan

30:58.164 --> 31:01.499
- for a couple days.
- They're on the run.

31:01.501 --> 31:03.733
Letting things cool off for a bit.

31:03.735 --> 31:05.836
Santos is a coward.

31:05.838 --> 31:08.005
Maybe. I don't know.

31:08.007 --> 31:11.408
He's got no balls. Not like you.

31:11.410 --> 31:13.910
You're not afraid of anything.

31:13.912 --> 31:15.446
You and me,

31:15.448 --> 31:17.081
we should start our own pack.

31:17.083 --> 31:19.083
It doesn't work like that.
You're not one of us.

31:19.085 --> 31:21.651
But I could be. Just one little bite

31:21.653 --> 31:23.887
and I could be your werewolf queen.

31:23.889 --> 31:26.857
We'd kick ass, like Bonnie and Clyde.

31:26.859 --> 31:28.758
You know how that ends, right?

31:28.760 --> 31:30.961
Nobody gets out alive.

31:30.963 --> 31:32.829
It's the living part that counts.

31:32.831 --> 31:34.498
I want to live like you.

31:34.500 --> 31:35.966
And I want you to live, period.

31:35.968 --> 31:38.001
Think about it. We could have it all.

31:38.003 --> 31:41.070
- You could be Alpha.
- You really think I care about that?

31:41.072 --> 31:43.672
You could settle do...
<i>We</i> could settle down.

31:43.674 --> 31:47.076
The house on the hill don't mean
nothing if you're not in it.

31:47.078 --> 31:49.445
No, it's too dangerous. Forget it.

31:49.447 --> 31:51.547
You're assuming I'll die.

31:51.549 --> 31:53.549
I'm a fighter, baby.

31:53.551 --> 31:55.618
Look,

31:55.620 --> 31:57.720
you're my girl.

31:57.722 --> 31:59.655
And I knew from the first time I saw you

31:59.657 --> 32:01.690
that you were a fighter, but...

32:01.692 --> 32:03.358
this ain't a fight you can win.

32:05.461 --> 32:06.962
(Whispering)
Baby...

32:09.532 --> 32:11.833
I'm going for nachos.

32:24.213 --> 32:26.948
- Any idea which way he went?
- Give me a second.

32:31.654 --> 32:33.487
Cain went West.

32:33.489 --> 32:35.156
Let's go get him.

32:37.893 --> 32:40.261
Are these your paintings?

32:40.263 --> 32:42.663
Yes. They're beautiful.

32:42.665 --> 32:43.964
Thank you.

32:45.733 --> 32:47.801
You remind me of Turner.

32:47.803 --> 32:49.770
You know your art.

32:49.772 --> 32:52.039
I didn't always live in Bear Valley.

32:52.041 --> 32:54.708
We had great museums in Baltimore.

32:58.713 --> 33:00.847
Would you like to have a seat?

33:07.188 --> 33:11.024
You have some information
about Mr. Braxton?

33:11.026 --> 33:13.393
His body was found just
inside town limits.

33:13.395 --> 33:14.962
His throat was cut,

33:14.964 --> 33:17.497
which now makes this a
homicide investigation.

33:17.499 --> 33:19.899
First wolf attacks, and now a murder.

33:19.901 --> 33:21.867
You don't think they're related?

33:21.869 --> 33:24.971
We'll see where the
investigation takes us.

33:24.973 --> 33:27.474
What does this have to do with my son?

33:27.476 --> 33:30.276
You know Braxton was talking about
coming up here to confront him.

33:30.278 --> 33:33.045
I understand he was very intoxicated
when he made those statements.

33:33.047 --> 33:35.314
He had had a few drinks.

33:35.316 --> 33:37.182
From my limited experience,

33:37.184 --> 33:39.051
when a man's had a few too many drinks,

33:39.053 --> 33:40.920
he tends to be a bit boastful.

33:40.922 --> 33:42.755
And then when he sobers up,

33:42.757 --> 33:45.357
he gets a little more rational.

33:45.359 --> 33:48.127
Now, the last time any
of us saw Mr. Braxton

33:48.129 --> 33:50.862
was the day that we found
that poor dead child.

33:55.268 --> 33:57.236
All these artifacts...

33:57.238 --> 33:59.638
you must have a well-used passport.

33:59.640 --> 34:02.441
Actually, most of them
were acquired by my son.

34:02.443 --> 34:04.976
He has a doctorate in anthropology.

34:04.978 --> 34:07.612
Is Clayton your son by birth?

34:07.614 --> 34:09.748
That's a... an interesting question.

34:09.750 --> 34:12.684
You just... you don't look old
enough to have a son that age.

34:12.686 --> 34:15.186
Ha. You're trying to flatter me.

34:15.188 --> 34:16.286
(Chuckling)

34:16.289 --> 34:18.690
I actually brought him
here when he was eight.

34:18.692 --> 34:20.925
So now he's a professor.

34:20.927 --> 34:22.926
You must be very proud.

34:22.928 --> 34:25.496
I'm very proud of all of my family.

34:27.466 --> 34:30.966
( ♪ )

34:40.344 --> 34:41.745
Clay: Good call.

34:41.746 --> 34:44.882
- Tracks pointed the way.
- If we go in there

34:44.884 --> 34:47.217
we'll end with a lot
of collateral damage.

34:47.219 --> 34:49.719
We should wait for him to come out.

34:49.722 --> 34:51.755
No.

34:51.757 --> 34:54.291
I wait for him to come out.

34:57.772 --> 35:01.272
( ♪ )

35:06.248 --> 35:07.815
Having a party?

35:07.817 --> 35:09.449
I am now.

35:14.088 --> 35:16.056
(Screeching)

35:17.425 --> 35:18.992
You're going to pay for that.

35:26.238 --> 35:29.770
You really think you can
take me one-on-one?

35:29.772 --> 35:31.271
Easy.

35:31.273 --> 35:33.373
You're dumb and you're slow.

35:33.375 --> 35:35.875
(Mixed grunting)

35:43.317 --> 35:45.051
I'm done screwing around!

35:52.126 --> 35:54.994
I knew you wouldn't be too
far behind your bitch.

35:54.996 --> 35:57.263
(Grunting)

35:57.265 --> 36:00.299
(Cracking)
Don't kill him, we need him.

36:00.301 --> 36:01.500
(Grunting, panting)

36:01.502 --> 36:03.068
Clay!

36:03.070 --> 36:05.504
Clay, Clay,

36:05.506 --> 36:06.772
look at me!

36:06.774 --> 36:08.974
You can't kill him!

36:08.976 --> 36:10.810
(Panting)

36:18.417 --> 36:19.985
I didn't kill him.

36:21.654 --> 36:23.788
Let's get him out of here.

36:25.091 --> 36:26.691
Thanks for your time.

36:26.693 --> 36:28.894
I'll have Clay call
as soon as he returns.

36:28.896 --> 36:31.863
I don't mind driving back
out here to talk to him.

36:31.865 --> 36:34.332
I'd like to see the rest of the house.

36:34.334 --> 36:36.167
Maybe some other time,

36:36.169 --> 36:38.670
when you're not in the middle
of a murder investigation.

36:38.672 --> 36:41.072
- Yes. - Yeah.
- Thanks again.

36:45.043 --> 36:47.278
(Panting)

36:50.749 --> 36:52.783
She's gone.

36:54.086 --> 36:55.887
(Groaning)

36:57.189 --> 36:59.623
- Stay here, I'll grab the med kit.
- Okay.

37:11.369 --> 37:13.169
(Cellphone ringing)

37:15.640 --> 37:17.240
It's Jeremy Danvers.

37:18.476 --> 37:20.176
I'll call him back.

37:20.178 --> 37:22.345
Babe, it's Jeremy.

37:22.347 --> 37:23.914
You better take this.

37:27.484 --> 37:29.552
- Hello?
Jeremy: <i>- Logan...</i>

37:29.554 --> 37:32.322
things have escalated.

37:32.324 --> 37:34.124
Antonio is dead.

37:36.493 --> 37:37.794
Everything okay?

37:39.463 --> 37:42.732
<i>Logan, are you there?</i>

37:42.734 --> 37:45.067
- What happened?
<i>- The Mutts attacked us.</i>

37:45.069 --> 37:47.937
- Are you all right?
- Yeah, I will be.

37:47.939 --> 37:49.806
I need you to come back.

37:51.508 --> 37:53.809
I'm so sorry, just...

37:53.811 --> 37:55.945
I'll come as soon as I can.

37:55.947 --> 37:58.314
Clay is bringing Cain in
for questioning.

37:58.316 --> 37:59.949
The rest of the Mutts
are still out there

37:59.951 --> 38:02.717
<i>and they're on a murderous spree.</i>

38:02.719 --> 38:04.753
I want the family back here as a Pack.

38:04.755 --> 38:08.290
Logan: <i>Just... I have some things I
need to take care of here first.</i>

38:09.859 --> 38:13.562
Tell Nick I'm...

38:13.564 --> 38:15.096
<i>My thoughts are with him.</i>

38:21.170 --> 38:23.438
What's wrong?

38:23.440 --> 38:25.774
Just more family issues.

38:25.776 --> 38:27.942
How long are you going
to be gone this time?

38:29.578 --> 38:31.446
I'm not going anywhere.

38:45.594 --> 38:47.294
Wow.

38:47.296 --> 38:48.929
Always wondered what
this place looked like.

38:48.931 --> 38:51.431
Wait until you see the
guest suite downstairs.

38:57.839 --> 38:59.873
Jeremy: Elena.

39:05.380 --> 39:06.480
You were successful.

39:08.316 --> 39:10.150
We got lucky.

39:10.152 --> 39:13.786
I think that we deserved a
little bit of luck today,

39:13.788 --> 39:15.155
don't you?

39:18.492 --> 39:20.459
Jeremy...

39:22.930 --> 39:26.499
I may have lost a little bit
more blood than I thought.

39:28.836 --> 39:31.771
I will be good as new in the morning.

39:31.773 --> 39:34.006
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

39:35.475 --> 39:37.809
(Cellphone chiming)

39:40.414 --> 39:43.049
Philip?

39:43.051 --> 39:45.384
Now's not the time.

39:45.386 --> 39:47.386
Call him back.

39:47.388 --> 39:49.087
Call him back.

39:49.089 --> 39:52.190
You need to assure him
that you're all right.

39:52.192 --> 39:54.826
Otherwise he may be on the next
train out here to Bear Valley.

39:54.828 --> 39:57.529
No, I'm more worried
about you right now.

39:57.531 --> 39:59.798
Don't be.

39:59.800 --> 40:01.199
Call him.

40:09.375 --> 40:11.242
(Soft gasp)

40:18.517 --> 40:20.151
(Grunt)

40:29.861 --> 40:32.529
What now, tough guy?

40:32.531 --> 40:34.999
Now you tell me the
location of the warehouse.

40:36.668 --> 40:38.902
Doesn't ring a bell.

40:38.904 --> 40:41.938
The place you and Marsten
and your psycho buddy

40:41.940 --> 40:44.841
were talking about the
other day at the motel.

40:44.843 --> 40:47.411
Oh, yeah. The motel.

40:47.413 --> 40:49.413
Marsten thought he smelled
you and the bitch.

40:51.116 --> 40:54.151
You like the little gift
we left behind for you?

40:54.153 --> 40:56.219
(Grunting)

40:57.521 --> 40:59.122
I guarantee

40:59.124 --> 41:01.024
you will tell me where to find them

41:01.026 --> 41:02.492
before I'm done with you.

41:08.599 --> 41:10.934
(Remote phone ringing)

41:10.936 --> 41:13.536
Philip: (On phone) <i>Hi.</i>

41:13.538 --> 41:15.404
Hey, it's me.

41:15.406 --> 41:18.073
Where are you?

41:18.075 --> 41:19.475
Are you all right?

41:21.311 --> 41:22.645
I'm okay.

41:25.315 --> 41:27.316
Look, I'm...

41:27.318 --> 41:29.384
I'm sorry for leaving you like that.

41:29.386 --> 41:32.054
<i>It was a horrible thing</i>
<i>for me to do to you.</i>

41:32.056 --> 41:33.622
Yeah, I'd have to agree.

41:35.525 --> 41:39.061
I just... I haven't had
to deal with a death...

41:39.063 --> 41:41.930
in my family since my parents.

41:44.333 --> 41:46.968
And being with your
family at the wedding,

41:46.970 --> 41:49.504
it all just sort of...

41:49.506 --> 41:51.239
hit me hard.

41:51.241 --> 41:53.375
<i>I just needed to take some time</i>

41:53.377 --> 41:55.644
<i>to work through a few things.</i>

41:57.480 --> 41:59.181
It's all right.

41:59.183 --> 42:01.549
<i>Maybe one day you'll let me help you</i>

42:01.551 --> 42:03.785
<i>work through those things.</i>

42:03.787 --> 42:05.720
That would be nice.

42:05.722 --> 42:08.056
<i>Are you back at Bear Valley?</i>

42:09.491 --> 42:10.858
For now.

42:10.860 --> 42:14.195
Is Logan there,
or someone you can talk to?

42:15.430 --> 42:17.331
Elena: Some of the cousins are here.

42:17.333 --> 42:21.134
We're... we're dealing with it together.

42:26.308 --> 42:29.076
I hope you stay with me through this.

42:31.513 --> 42:33.146
You know I will.

42:33.148 --> 42:35.215
<i>I'll see you soon.</i>

42:37.418 --> 42:38.685
Yeah.

42:44.325 --> 42:46.159
(Impact thud)

42:47.494 --> 42:48.595
Jeremy?

42:51.998 --> 42:54.367
Jeremy!

42:54.369 --> 42:55.702
Hey...

42:55.704 --> 42:57.669
Jeremy...

42:57.671 --> 42:58.870
Nick!

42:58.872 --> 43:01.473
(Suspenseful ♪)

43:01.475 --> 43:04.876
( ♪ )

43:04.878 --> 43:07.446
This can't be just blood loss.

